SIMPLE: impacted
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impacted
<hw>Im*pact"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Driven
together or close.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <fld>(Dentistry)</fld>
<def>Grown in an abnormal direction so that it is wedged against another
tooth and cannot erupt normally; -- of teeth, especially the third
molar; <as>as, to extract an <ex>impacted</ex> third
molar</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Impacted fracture</b></col> <fld>(Surg.)</fld>, <cd>a
fracture in which the fragments are driven into each other so as to be
immovable.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impaction</ent>⟦br⟧
